## Setup

```bash
nix develop path:.
uv venv
uv pip install -e ".[dev]"
uv pip install -e tools/flake8-plugin/
pre-commit install
make check
```

## Development

| Command | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `make lint` | Run Ruff and custom ANV lint rules |
| `make format` | Check Ruff formatting |
| `make typecheck` | Run mypy |
| `make security` | Scan for secrets |
| `make test` | Run Python tests |
| `make coverage` | Run tests with coverage thresholds |
| `make deadcode` | Detect unused code |
| `make crap` | Compute CRAP scores |
| `make audit` | Audit dependencies |
| `make mutate` | Run mutation testing |
| `make check` | Run tier 1 and tier 2 validation |
| `make quality` | Run all validation, including mutation testing |
| `make fix` | Auto-fix lint and formatting issues |

## Anvil-generated validation gates

Anvil wires validation through the generated `Makefile`. Run `make check`
before handoff or push. Run `make quality` at the final quality boundary when
you need the mutation gate too.

`AGENTS.md` gives coding agents repo-local instructions. `.anvil.lock` records
the Anvil version, toolchain versions, generated files, and checksums used for
safe re-scaffold decisions. Do not edit `.anvil.lock` by hand; rerun `anvil
init` or `anvil doctor` instead.

The seed/reference code demonstrates conventions to follow: module structure,
tests, typed errors, constants, enums, and structured logging.

## Project Structure

